51.9	Courage	Courage	Courage (also bravery, boldness, fearlessness, mettle, fortitude, or intrepidity) is the ability to confront fear, pain, danger, uncertainty, or intimidation. Courage is acting in spite of fear. "Physical courage" is courage in the face of physical pain, hardship, death, or threat of death, while "moral courage" is the ability to act rightly in the face of popular opposition, shame, scandal, or discouragement.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/54/Fortitude.jpg/220px-Fortitude.jpg
